data.text: Earl Baldwin (January 11, 1901â October 9, 1970) was an American screenwriter. He was born in Newark, New Jersey. During his career he wrote more than 50 produced screenplays, including Wild Boys of the Road, Brother Orchid, and Abbott and Costello's Africa Screams. He died at age 69 in Hollywood, California.
